        "alt": "Amber Featherboat Harbour, an open cosy storybook setting.",
        "prompt": "Use case: illustration-story. Asset type: 16:9 Story Stones game backdrop. Primary request: Amber Featherboat Harbour, a gentle fantasy harbour with feather-shaped boats, lily-pad docks, painted boathouses, and a wide clear quay; amber leaves twinkling at the edges. Style/medium: cosy children's picture-book illustration, hand-painted gouache and coloured-pencil texture on warm paper, chunky charcoal contours, charming imperfect brush marks, matching the approved Story Stones seed 1337 art direction. Composition/framing: wide 16:9 view with a broad uncluttered lower-centre performance clearing and environmental detail around the edges. Lighting/mood: honey-gold light, gentle, magical, welcoming for ages 3–7. Constraints: environment only; preserve a clear floor for three separately composited story-stone sprites. Avoid: characters, creatures, people, food or loose hero objects in the performance area, text, letters, logo, watermark, UI, border, collage, photorealism, 3D.",
        "seed": 457089530,
        "workflow": "krea2-turbo-t2i",
        "width": 1344,
        "height": 768,
        "steps": 8,
        "cfg": 1
      },
      "beats": [
        {
          "id": "beginning",
          "narrator": "story-dragon--magic-rock--rose-beginning",
          "text": "Friendly Dragon reached Amber Featherboat Harbour, where the featherboats had drifted from their docks. Friendly Dragon warmed the air."
        },
        {
          "id": "complication",
          "narrator": "story-dragon--magic-rock--rose-complication",
          "text": "Magic Rose joined just as the harbour breeze changed direction. Friendly Dragon fanned its orange wings, and Magic Rose pointed with its stem, making a path to shore."
        },
        {
          "id": "resolution",
          "narrator": "story-dragon--magic-rock--rose-resolution",
          "text": "One thing remained: Magic Rock rumbled the pieces into line. That helped, and the boats bobbed beside the quay again. Bright flags rose while water clapped against the steps."
        }
      ]
    },
